The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Editor held
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           Editor held
                            
	Hyderabad, June 24: The editor of Telugu daily Andhra Jyothy and its two reporters were arrested today in a case filed under the SC Act.         
	Manda Krishna Madiga, the leader of the Scheduled Caste Association of MRPS, had filed the case against editor K. Srinivas and the others for an article published in May that made disparaging comments on Dalit leaders.         
	The newspaper is known for its anti-Congress government stance.                                                                                                                                                                          
